\newlabel{fig:main_results}{{1}{3}{Single-run diagnostic. (a) Final $20 \times 20$ conflict-memory map. Activation is sparse and concentrated in one dominant hotspot with a few weaker secondary cells. (b) Logged improvement-ratio values by instance index. Most values are at or extremely near zero, with one harmful outlier near $-0.2$. Together, the panels show that CMA learned stable spatial structure but rarely converted it into better outcomes}{figure.1}{}}
